   "source": [
    "# Numerical Project 2a – Illustration of Itô Formula\n",
    "\n",
    "This project illustrates the Itô formula using simulations of Brownian motion.\n",
    "\n",
    "The Itô formula states that for a twice differentiable function \\(f\\),\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "f(B_t) - f(B_0) = \\int_0^t f'(B_s)dB_s + \\frac{1}{2}\\int_0^t f''(B_s)ds\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "We simulate Brownian motion paths and compare both sides of the identity for two functions:\n",
    "\n",
    "- \\(f(x) = x^4\\)\n",
    "- \\(f(x) = \\sin(x)\\)\n",
    "\n",
    "The simulations use a time discretization of \\(0.001\\)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "fbe5ad3b-f61d-4b3a-804d-e59468947ad6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fc0716e2-1a0b-4018-8400-3f7ba773ac82",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Simulation of Brownian Motion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "54df676d-ce0b-4c53-abdd-d34539b6d908",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def brownian(interval, step):\n",
    "\n",
    "    n = int(interval/step)\n",
    "\n",
    "    B = [0]\n",
    "\n",
    "    for i in range(n):\n",
    "        B.append(B[-1] + np.sqrt(step)*np.random.standard_normal())\n",
    "\n",
    "    return np.array(B)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2564dc52-cd5c-485d-a83a-13d1acfb42a7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part (a): Case \\(f(x)=x^4\\)\n",
    "\n",
    "For \\(f(x)=x^4\\), we have\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "f'(x)=4x^3, \\quad f''(x)=12x^2\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The Itô formula becomes\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "B_t^4 = \\int_0^t 4B_s^3 dB_s + \\int_0^t 6B_s^2 ds\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "which can be written as\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "B_t^4 - \\int_0^t 6B_s^2 ds = \\int_0^t 4B_s^3 dB_s\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "We simulate both sides and compare the resulting paths."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "c1b77388-e95b-4741-a1cd-89b3e251e339",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "step = 0.001\n",
    "T = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "B = brownian(T,step)\n",
    "\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0,T,len(B))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "86b1a2ab-6600-45e5-8437-19c247ce67ca",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simulation of the Itô Integral\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\int_0^t 4B_s^3 dB_s\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "f71a1519-776a-44a7-ac39-e5d1ef037000",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Ito = [0]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(1,len(B)):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    increment = 4*(B[i-1]**3)*(B[i]-B[i-1])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Ito.append(Ito[-1] + increment)\n",
    "\n",
    "Ito = np.array(Ito)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "e0d00a85-3fee-4f8d-8de7-6f5b0fda3ead",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simulation of the Riemann Integral\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\int_0^t 6B_s^2 ds\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "feed328b-c3ce-465c-aaee-c6aedc9c05bf",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Riemann = [0]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(1,len(B)):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    increment = 6*(B[i-1]**2)*step\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Riemann.append(Riemann[-1] + increment)\n",
    "\n",
    "Riemann = np.array(Riemann)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "05d9ce50-2568-4bd6-9d83-e9b2fd64d109",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Process\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "B_t^4 - \\int_0^t 6B_s^2 ds\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "877a25f5-cdc1-4a6e-b1cc-30073c705ab0",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Left = B**4 - Riemann"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bab2faf0-bbeb-4900-b677-71cbf5968935",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Comparison of both sides"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "d6f3010b-4798-4248-aec6-2a0bf151e36c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9,5))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(t,Left,label=r\"$B_t^4 - \\int_0^t 6B_s^2 ds$\",linewidth=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(t,Ito,label=r\"$\\int_0^t 4B_s^3 dB_s$\",linewidth=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"t\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"value\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.title(\"Illustration of Ito formula for f(x)=x^4\")\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a950bff4-b1e5-4071-8127-aae6c9dd7cc9",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Discussion\n",
    "\n",
    "The two simulated paths are almost identical, which confirms the Itô identity\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "B_t^4 =\n",
    "\\int_0^t 4B_s^3 dB_s +\n",
    "\\int_0^t 6B_s^2 ds\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The small differences between the curves are due to the discretization error in the numerical approximation."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "3ced4bb6-17e6-42b8-b682-d7e8682eb9ad",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Part (b): Case \\(f(x)=\\sin(x)\\)\n",
    "\n",
    "For \\(f(x)=\\sin(x)\\), we have\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "f'(x)=\\cos(x), \\qquad f''(x)=-\\sin(x)\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The Itô formula becomes\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sin(B_t)=\\int_0^t \\cos(B_s)\\,dB_s-\\frac12\\int_0^t \\sin(B_s)\\,ds\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "which can be written as\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sin(B_t)+\\frac12\\int_0^t \\sin(B_s)\\,ds\n",
    "=\n",
    "\\int_0^t \\cos(B_s)\\,dB_s\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "We simulate both sides and compare the paths."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "ccba7d8c-861e-476d-88f3-4a9bc0c90cfc",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "np.random.seed(0)\n",
    "\n",
    "step = 0.001\n",
    "T = 1\n",
    "\n",
    "B = brownian(T, step)\n",
    "\n",
    "t = np.linspace(0, T, len(B))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "03a5f31e-0602-4a4a-adde-fe96ab1a25ea",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simulation of the Itô integral\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\int_0^t \\cos(B_s)\\,dB_s\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "f83bb1de-cc21-417f-a920-684aa6ee747a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Ito2 = [0]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(1, len(B)):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    increment = np.cos(B[i-1]) * (B[i] - B[i-1])\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Ito2.append(Ito2[-1] + increment)\n",
    "\n",
    "Ito2 = np.array(Ito2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "134994a5-6beb-4831-9633-719c32b106e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Simulation of the Riemann integral\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\frac12\\int_0^t \\sin(B_s)\\,ds\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "1d0693bc-5297-4045-a137-e53e9bcde1aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Riemann2 = [0]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(1, len(B)):\n",
    "    \n",
    "    increment = 0.5 * np.sin(B[i-1]) * step\n",
    "    \n",
    "    Riemann2.append(Riemann2[-1] + increment)\n",
    "\n",
    "Riemann2 = np.array(Riemann2)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "aae3ab7d-9339-4611-bc8d-8df48d68d61b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Process\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sin(B_t)+\\frac12\\int_0^t \\sin(B_s)\\,ds\n",
    "$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "e4d375f6-d52b-428a-a199-1be38cba7ef9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "Left2 = np.sin(B) + Riemann2"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1f2d3bf8-aaaa-4a03-8c90-093363e9eeac",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Comparison of both sides"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 19,
   "id": "3d853451-47cb-463d-b90f-e095819e2bd6",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(9,5))\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(t, Left2, label=r\"$\\sin(B_t)+\\frac{1}{2}\\int_0^t \\sin(B_s)\\,ds$\", linewidth=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(t, Ito2, label=r\"$\\int_0^t \\cos(B_s)\\,dB_s$\", linewidth=2)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.xlabel(\"t\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel(\"value\")\n",
    "plt.title(\"Illustration of Ito formula for f(x)=sin(x)\")\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.grid(alpha=0.3)\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d9af399c-662b-461a-9cd2-b7d870861f22",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Discussion\n",
    "\n",
    "The two simulated paths are almost identical, confirming the Itô identity\n",
    "\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\\sin(B_t) = \\int_0^t \\cos(B_s)dB_s - \\frac{1}{2}\\int_0^t \\sin(B_s)ds\n",
    "$$\n",
    "\n",
    "The small differences between the curves are due to discretization errors introduced by the numerical approximation of the integrals."
   ]
  }
